        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 9:22PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM CDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm 7 miles southwest of Uniontown, or 16 miles northeast of
Erie, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Marmaton, Uniontown, Redfield, Hiattville, Petersburg,
Hammond, Devon, Garland, Porterville, and Pawnee Station.

Nickel size hail was reported with this storm in Savonburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
